Data Import_Diversity

The taxonomy, feature, and metadata tables were loaded into R and placed in a phyloseq object.

#Import ASV table.
otumat <- read.csv("QIIME2/feature_table/feature_table.txt", sep="",row.names=1) %>% 
          as.matrix() %>% otu_table(taxa_are_rows = T)

#Import taxonomy table.
taxmat <- read.csv(file="Processed_data/taxonomy_diversity.csv", header=T, sep=",", row.names=1) %>% 
          as.matrix() %>% tax_table()
stopifnot(rownames(otumat) == rownames(taxmat))

#Import metadata.
metadata <- read.csv(file="Processed_data/meta_data_1.csv", sep=",", header=T,row.names=1) %>%  sample_data()

# Make sure your sample names are consistent across your OTU/feature table and your metadata file.
# sample_names(otumat)
# sample_names(metadata)
# Import tree file 
rooted_tree <- read_tree("QIIME2/rooted_tree/tree.nwk",errorIfNULL=FALSE)

# Create Phyloseq object
physeq <- merge_phyloseq(otumat,taxmat,metadata,rooted_tree)

colnames(tax_table(physeq)) <- c("Kingdom", "Phylum", "Class", 
                                     "Order", "Family", "Genus","Species") 
sample_data(physeq)$Group <- factor(sample_data(physeq)$Group, levels = c('Mock', "CP",'EM',"NEm","NEs"))
sample_data(physeq)$Site <- factor(sample_data(physeq)$Site, levels = c('Ileum', 'Cecum'))
sample_data(physeq)$Trial <- factor(sample_data(physeq)$Trial, levels = c('T3', 'T5'))

# Subset sample based on site and trial
physeq_Ile <- subset_samples(physeq, Site == "Ileum" & Trial == "T3"& SampleID != "T3.P45" & SampleID != "T3.P27" & SampleID != "T3.P55")

physeq_Ile<-subset_taxa(physeq_Ile, Kingdom != "Eukaryota")

# Remove ASVs present less than 5% of the sample
physeq <- physeq_Ile %>%
  prune_taxa(rowSums(otu_table(physeq_Ile) != 0) >= 4, .) # 74*0.05

#Normalize data using CSS method
# Convert phyloseq object to metageomeSeq object
metaSeq <- phyloseq_to_metagenomeSeq(physeq)
# Calculate pth quantile
p <- cumNormStatFast(metaSeq) 
# CSS normalization
meta_sub <- cumNorm(metaSeq, p = p) 
# Pull OTU table out of metagenomeSeq
otu_data <- as.data.frame(MRcounts(meta_sub, norm = T, log = F))   
bacteria <- physeq
otu_table(bacteria) <- otu_table(otu_data, taxa_are_rows = T)

Weighted UniFrac

clr <- c("#868686","#0068B0","#F2C600","yellowgreen","#CB4944")

set.seed(42)
weighted <- ordinate(
  physeq = bacteria, 
  method = "PCoA", 
  distance = "unifrac",weight=TRUE)

plot_scree(weighted, "Scree plot, unifrac/PCoA")

weighted_table <- phyloseq::distance(bacteria, 'wunifrac')
sampledf <- data.frame(sample_data(bacteria))

adonis2(weighted_table ~ Group, data = sampledf)
## Permutation test for adonis under reduced model
## Terms added sequentially (first to last)
## Permutation: free
## Number of permutations: 999
## 
## adonis2(formula = weighted_table ~ Group, data = sampledf)
##          Df SumOfSqs      R2      F Pr(>F)    
## Group     4  1.16162 0.63499 28.704  0.001 ***
## Residual 66  0.66773 0.36501                  
## Total    70  1.82935 1.00000                  
## ---
## Signif. codes:  0 '***' 0.001 '**' 0.01 '*' 0.05 '.' 0.1 ' ' 1
perm <- pairwise.perm.manova(weighted_table, sampledf$Group, nperm = 999,p.method = 'none', R2=TRUE)

Phylum statistical analysis

sem <- function(x) sd(x)/sqrt(length(x))

phylum_relabund <- bacteria %>%                  
  tax_glom(taxrank = "Phylum") %>%                    # group at phylum level
  transform_sample_counts(function(x) {x/sum(x)} ) %>% # Transform to rel. abundance
  psmelt()  # Melt to long format

phylum_relabund$Phylum <- reorder(phylum_relabund$Phylum, phylum_relabund$Abundance)
phylum_relabund$Percent <- phylum_relabund$Abundance * 100
data <- subset(phylum_relabund, Phylum == 'Firmicutes')
data$Sample <- reorder(data$Sample, data$Abundance)
phylum_relabund$Sample <- factor(phylum_relabund$Sample, levels = rev(data$Sample))

# Pull out the Sample, Percent, Group, and Phylum columns
# Collapse Relabund
mean_phylum <-  phylum_relabund[,c(2,4,13,14)] #Sample, Group, Phylum, Percent

# Spread into a data frame where each phyla has its own column
mean_phylum <- spread(mean_phylum, Phylum, Percent) 
#mean_phylum<- mean_phylum[,-c(1,2,3)]
# Remove Sample and Group columns
mean <- mean_phylum[,-c(1,2)] 
 # Convert NAs to 0s
mean[is.na(mean)] <- 0   
mean_phylum[is.na(mean_phylum)] <- 0 

# Calculate the mean of each phylum in each Trt
mean_phylum_2 <- aggregate(mean, by=list(mean_phylum$Group), mean)  

# Transform so that rows are phyla
mean_phylum_3 <- t(mean_phylum_2)
mean_phylum_3 <- as.data.frame(mean_phylum_3)                           
colnames(mean_phylum_3) <-mean_phylum_3[1,]
mean_phylum_3 <-mean_phylum_3[-1,]

# Calcualte the standard deviation of each phylum
sem_phylum <- aggregate(mean, by=list(mean_phylum$Group), sem)         
sem_phylum_2 <- t(sem_phylum)
sem_phylum_2 <- as.data.frame(sem_phylum_2)
colnames(sem_phylum_2) <-sem_phylum_2[1,]
sem_phylum_2 <-sem_phylum_2[-1,]

# Run Statistics
# Pull out the column names that include the list of phyla
phyla <- colnames(mean_phylum) 
# Remova the Sample and lesion score from th elist
phyla <- phyla[-c(1:2)] 

# Create empty data frame for loop
Phyla_P <- data.frame(matrix(nrow = length(phyla), ncol = 1))
 # Label the rows and columns of the empty data frame
rownames(Phyla_P) <- phyla                                           
colnames(Phyla_P) <- "P"

Phyla_P <- NULL

for (i in 1:length(phyla)){
  k <- kruskal.test(mean_phylum[,2+i] ~ mean_phylum[,2], mean_phylum)
  data <- data.frame(Phylum = phyla[i], P = k[3])
  Phyla_P <- rbind(Phyla_P, data)
}


Phyla_P$BH <- p.adjust(Phyla_P$p.value, method = 'BH')
rownames(Phyla_P) <-Phyla_P$Phylum

Phyla_P <- cbind(Phyla_P, mean_phylum_3,sem_phylum_2)
Phyla_P

feature_relanund <- bacteria %>%

feature_relanund$Percent <- feature_relanund$Abundance * 100

feature_relanund <- feature_relanund[,c(2,4,19,20)]
#genus_relabund <- spread(genus_relabund, Genus, Percent)
feature_relanund<-feature_relanund %>%
  distinct(Sample, ASVs, .keep_all = TRUE) %>%
  spread(ASVs, Percent)

feature_relanund <- feature_relanund[,-1]
feature_relanund[is.na(feature_relanund)] <- 0

feature_relanund_2 <- feature_relanund %>%
  group_by(Group) %>%
  summarise_each(funs(mean)) 

# Copy all columns from 'genus_relabund_2' to new object 'pie'.
pie <- feature_relanund_2[,c(1:429)]

#Remove lowly abundant features, leaving only the top 20 most abundant.
count <- pie[,-c(1:409)]
#Create the column 'Sums', which lists the sum of the top 20. 
count$Sums <- apply(count, 1, sum)
#Calculate the sum of the now-removed lowly abundant features by subtraction.
count$Others <- (100 - count$Sums)
#Remove the sums column. 
count <- count[,-21]
#Add the 'Gender' and 'BW' columns back in.
count$Group <- pie$Group

long_mean <- gather(count, ASVs, Abundance, 1:21)

          as.matrix() %>% tax_table()

stopifnot(rownames(otumat) == rownames(taxmat))

#Import metadata.

physeq <- merge_phyloseq(otumat,taxmat,metadata)

colnames(tax_table(physeq)) <- c("Kingdom", "Phylum", "Class", 
                                     "Order", "Family", "Genus","Species") 
sample_data(physeq)$Group <- factor(sample_data(physeq)$Group, levels = c('Mock', 'CP',"EM","NEm","NEs"))
sample_data(physeq)$Site <- factor(sample_data(physeq)$Site, levels = c('Ileum', 'Cecum'))
sample_data(physeq)$Trial <- factor(sample_data(physeq)$Trial, levels = c('T3', 'T5'))

# Subset sample based on site and trial
physeq_Ile <- subset_samples(physeq, Site == "Ileum" & Trial == "T3"& SampleID != "T3.P34")
physeq_Ile<-subset_taxa(physeq_Ile, Kingdom != "Eukaryota" & Phylum != "Cyanobacteria" & Phylum !="Tenericutes")

Remove OTUs that sum to 0 and a relative abundance less than 0.01%

# Remove ASVs present less than 5% of the sample
physeq <- physeq_Ile %>%
  prune_taxa(rowSums(otu_table(physeq_Ile) != 0) >= 4, .) # 69*0.05

#Normalize data using CSS method
# Convert phyloseq object to metageomeSeq object
metaSeq <- phyloseq_to_metagenomeSeq(physeq)
# Calculate pth quantile
p <- cumNormStatFast(metaSeq) 
## Default value being used.
# CSS normalization
meta_sub <- cumNorm(metaSeq, p = p) 
# Pull OTU table out of metagenomeSeq
otu_data <- as.data.frame(MRcounts(meta_sub, norm = T, log = F))   
bacteria <- physeq
otu_table(bacteria) <- otu_table(otu_data, taxa_are_rows = T)

#genus_relabund <- spread(genus_relabund, Genus, Percent)
genus_relabund$Group <- factor(genus_relabund$Group, levels = c("Mock","CP","EM","NEm","NEs"))

genus_relabund<-genus_relabund %>%
  distinct(Sample, Genus, .keep_all = TRUE) %>%
  spread(Genus, Percent)

# Input significantly different ASV_Mock_NE
Genus_DE <- read.csv("Processed_data/Lefse/T3/Ileum/DE_Genus.csv", sep=",", header=T)

ASV_mean <- genus_relabund[colnames(genus_relabund) %in% Genus_DE$feature]
ASV_mean[is.na(ASV_mean)] <- 0

median_ASV_2 <- aggregate(ASV_mean, by=list(genus_relabund$Group), median)
median_ASV_3<-as.data.frame(t(median_ASV_2))
colnames(median_ASV_3) <- median_ASV_3[1,]
median_ASV_3 <-median_ASV_3[-1,]
median_ASV_3 <- median_ASV_3 %>%
  mutate(across(where(is.character), as.numeric))

# Calculate fold change:
fold_change_data <- data.frame(
  ASV = rownames(median_ASV_3),
  Mock =median_ASV_3$Mock / median_ASV_3$Mock,
  CP = median_ASV_3$CP / median_ASV_3$Mock,
  EM = median_ASV_3$EM / median_ASV_3$Mock,
  NEm = median_ASV_3$NEm / median_ASV_3$Mock,
  NEs = median_ASV_3$NEs / median_ASV_3$Mock)

# Apply log2 transformation to the fold change columns
log2_trans <- fold_change_data %>%
  mutate(
    Mock = log2(Mock),
    CP = log2(CP),
    EM = log2(EM),
    NEm = log2(NEm),
    NEs = log2(NEs))

heat <-log2_trans

plotting

# Clustering
tree_y <- hclust(dist(heat[,-1]))
# get label order
tree_d <- fortify(tree_y)
tree_d <- subset(tree_d, isTip)
lab_order <- tree_d$label[order(tree_d$y,decreasing=F)]
heat3 <-heat[order(match(heat$ASV,lab_order)),]

### Make legend name ###
heat3$pre <- heat3$ASV
heat3 <- mutate(heat3, font_name=glue("<i>{pre}</i>"))

#
de_pic <- heat3[,c(2:6,8)]
de_pic$font_name  <- factor(de_pic$font_name ,levels = rev(c("<i>Escherichia</i>","<i>Clostridium</i>","<i>Romboutsia</i>","<i>Lactobacillus</i>","<i>Limosilactobacillus</i>","<i>Mediterraneibacter</i>","<i>Cuneatibacter</i>","<i>Blautia</i>","<i>Faecalibacterium</i>","<i>Enterococcus</i>","<i>Mammaliicoccus</i>","<i>Aerococcus</i>","<i>Bacillus</i>","<i>Corynebacterium</i>","<i>Sellimonas</i>","<i>Weissella</i>")))

### Over ###

#data format transformation
de_pic2 <- pivot_longer(de_pic,cols = colnames(de_pic[,-6]),
                       names_to = 'Group',values_to = 'abundance')
de_pic2$Group <- factor(de_pic2$Group,levels = c("Mock","CP","EM","NEm","NEs"))

 p1 <- ggplot(de_pic2,aes(x=Group,y=font_name))+
  #facet_grid(.~Group, space = "free_x")+
  geom_tile(aes(fill=abundance))+

   theme_bw()+
  theme(axis.ticks.y = element_blank(),
        axis.ticks.x = element_blank(),
        strip.background = element_blank(), # Remove facet box titile
        panel.grid = element_blank(),

        axis.title = element_blank(),

        legend.position = "right",
        legend.margin = margin(b=-5),
        legend.title = element_text(size = 8,color = "black"),
        plot.margin = margin(0,0,0,0)
  )
